WEBVTT

00:14.760 --> 00:15.880
CHAPTER V

00:16.640 --> 00:22.680
And I saw in the right hand of him that sat on the throne a book written within and on

00:22.680 --> 00:25.280
the back side, sealed with seven seals.

00:25.840 --> 00:29.820
And I saw a strong angel proclaiming with a loud voice,

00:30.580 --> 00:34.760
Who is worthy to open the book and to loose the seals thereof?

00:35.600 --> 00:42.400
And no man in heaven, nor in earth, nor under the earth, was able to open the book, neither to look

00:42.400 --> 00:49.720
thereon. And I wept much, because no man was found worthy to open and to read the book, neither to

00:49.720 --> 00:58.420
look thereon. And one of the elders saith unto me, Weep not, behold, the lion of the tribe of Judah,

00:58.700 --> 01:04.160
the root of David, hath prevailed to open the book and to loose the seven seals thereof.

01:04.720 --> 01:11.240
And I beheld, and lo, in the midst of the throne and of the four beasts, and in the midst of the

01:11.240 --> 01:19.580
elders, stood a lamb as it had been slain, having seven horns and seven eyes, which are the seven

01:19.580 --> 01:25.420
spirits of God sent forth into all the earth. And he came and took the book out of the right hand of

01:25.420 --> 01:31.220
him that sat upon the throne. And when he had taken the book, the four beasts and the four and

01:31.220 --> 01:37.320
twenty elders fell down before the lamb, having every one of them harps and golden vials full of

01:37.320 --> 01:45.240
odours, which are the prayers of saints. And they sung a new song, saying, Thou art worthy to take

01:45.240 --> 01:52.040
the book and to open the seals thereof. For thou wast slain, and hast redeemed us to God by thy

01:52.040 --> 01:58.940
blood out of every kindred and tongue and people and nation, and hast made us unto our God kings

01:58.940 --> 02:05.800
and priests, and we shall reign on the earth. And I beheld, and I heard the voice of many angels

02:05.800 --> 02:12.580
round about the throne and the beasts and the elders, and the number of them was ten thousand

02:12.580 --> 02:20.620
times ten thousand, and thousands of thousands, saying with a loud voice, Worthy is the lamb that

02:20.620 --> 02:27.360
was slain to receive power and riches and wisdom and strength and honour and glory and blessing,

02:28.120 --> 02:34.440
and every creature which is in heaven and on the earth and under the earth, and such as are in the

02:34.440 --> 02:42.040
sea and all that are in them, heard I saying, Blessing and honour and glory and power be unto

02:42.040 --> 02:49.520
him that sitteth upon the throne and unto the Lamb for ever and ever. And the four beasts said,

02:49.960 --> 02:57.600
Amen. And the four and twenty elders fell down and worshipped him that liveth for ever and ever.

02:58.920 --> 03:01.060
The End of Chapter 5

